function decode(encoded) {
    const n = encoded.length + 1;
    let total_xor = 0;
    for (let i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
        total_xor ^= i;
    }
    let encoded_xor = 0;
    for (let i = 1; i < n - 1; i += 2) {
        encoded_xor ^= encoded[i];
    }
    const perm = [total_xor ^ encoded_xor];
    for (let i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
        perm.push(perm[i - 1] ^ encoded[i - 1]);
    }
    return perm;
}
```


    1. Calculate the XOR of all integers from 1 to n (inclusive), and store it in the `total_xor` variable.
2. Calculate the XOR of all elements of the encoded array with odd indices (starting from index 1), and store it in the `encoded_xor` variable.
3. The first element of the perm array is calculated by XOR'ing `total_xor` and `encoded_xor`.
4. Loop through the range 1 to n-1 (inclusive) and calculate the rest of the perm array elements using the following formula: `perm[i] = perm[i - 1] ^ encoded[i - 1]`.
5. Return the reconstructed perm array.

